        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 13 at 2:35PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 234 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles southwest of Saguache, or 43 miles northwest of Alamosa, moving
east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Saguache and Moffat.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
